<span id="freeTextContainer365192042337562201"><i>The Closing of the American Mind,</i> a publishing phenomenon in hardcover, is now a paperback literary event. In this acclaimed number one national best-seller, one of our country&apos;s most distinguished political philosophers argues that the social/political crisis of 20th-century America is really an intellectual crisis. Allan Bloom&apos;s sweeping analysis is essential to understa</span>
  <span id="freeText365192042337562201" style="display:none"><i>The Closing of the American Mind,</i> a publishing phenomenon in hardcover, is now a paperback literary event. In this acclaimed number one national best-seller, one of our country's most distinguished political philosophers argues that the social/political crisis of 20th-century America is really an intellectual crisis. Allan Bloom's sweeping analysis is essential to understanding America today. It has fired the imagination of a public ripe for change.</span>
